{"lemma": "أَخْلَق", "slug": "أَخْلَق", "root": "خ.ل.ق", "root_slug": "خ-ل-ق", "root_link": "/words/roots/خ-ل-ق", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["verb"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 0}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n11384", "n11411"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AE%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%82"}}, "translations": {"en": "to wear out", "fa": "فرسوده کردن", "ur": "پھنسا دینا", "tr": "eskitmek", "id": "memakai", "bn": "পরা", "es": "desgastar", "fr": "user", "de": "abnutzen", "ru": "изнашивать", "zh": "磨损"}, "definition": null, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n11384", "headword_ar": "اخلق", "root": "xlq", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see 1, latter part, in three places. ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He had old and worn-out garments."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Axlqhu", "text_ar": "اخلقهُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He wore it out;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "namely, a garment; the verb being trans. as well as intrans. (S, Msb, K.) [Hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Axlq Ald~ahoru Al$~aYo'a", "text_ar": "اخلق الدَّهْرُ الشَّىْءَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Time wore out,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wasted, the thing."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) [Hence also,] one says to the beggar,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^axolaqota wajohaka", "text_ar": "اَخْلَقْتَ وَجْهَكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  (TA) [lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Thou hast worn out thy face;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thou hast used thy face for mean service"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "so that it has lost its grace,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "has become disgraced"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: and in like manner one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^uxoliqu lahu diyabaAjatiY", "text_ar": "اُخْلِقُ لَهُ دِيَبَاجَتِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wajohiY", "text_ar": "وَجْهِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yuxoliqu diybaAjatayohi", "text_ar": "يُخْلِقُ دِيبَاجَتَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He uses his face for mean service by begging."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Har pp. 15 and 476.) ―         -b2-  Also, (K,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Axlqhu vawobFA", "text_ar": "اخلقهُ ثَوْبًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He clad him with an old and worn-out garment."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AxlqinY vawobahu", "text_ar": "اخلقِنى ثَوْبَهُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He gave me his old and worn-out garment."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(JK.) And some say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Axlqhu xalaqFA", "text_ar": "اخلقهُ خَلَقًا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He gave him an old and worn-out garment."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ixolaAqN Alv~awobi", "text_ar": "اـِخْلَاقٌ الثَّوْبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The cutting out of the garment:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "whence the saying, to UmmKhálid,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aboliY waA^axoliqiY", "text_ar": "اَبْلِى وَاَخْلِقِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Wear out, and cut out"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "new]; or, as some relate it,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waA^axolifiY", "text_ar": "وَاَخْلِفِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e., “ and replace, ” which is the more likely. (TA.)       -A3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA A^axolaqahu", "text_ar": "مَا اَخْلَقَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^axoliqo bihi", "text_ar": "اَخْلِقْ بِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[have both of the following significations; though it is said that] the former signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "How likely is he,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it!"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(JK, TA;) and the latter,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "How well adapted"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "disposed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "how apt, meet, suited, suitable, fitted, fit, competent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "proper,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "how worthy, is he,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it! i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ajodiro", "text_ar": "اَجْدِرْ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bihi", "text_ar": "بِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHori bihi", "text_ar": "اَحْرِ بِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA. [See 4 in arts."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jdr", "text_ar": "جدر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HrY", "text_ar": "حرى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".])"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "K", "S"]}, {"entry_id": "n11411", "headword_ar": "اَخْلَقُ", "root": "xlq", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Smooth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(JK, K:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "smooth and solid;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K, TA;) applied in this sense to anything: (TA:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "smooth and firm:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(JK:) fem."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xaloqaA='u", "text_ar": "خَلْقَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (JK, S, K.) You say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HajarN A^axolaqu", "text_ar": "حَجَرٌ اَخْلَقُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Stone that is smooth"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and solid, upon which nothing makes an impression."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SaxorapN xaloqaA='u", "text_ar": "صَخْرَةٌ خَلْقَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A rock,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "great mass of stone, smooth"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and solid:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "free from crack and fracture."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "firosinN xaloqaA='u", "text_ar": "فِرْسِنٌ خَلْقَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A camel's foot in which is no crack."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ibn-'Abbád, K.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "haDobapN xaloqaA='u", "text_ar": "هَضْبَةٌ خَلْقَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A hill,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "destitute of herbage"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "vegetation."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Poor;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faqiyrN", "text_ar": "فَقِيرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) You say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rajulN A^axolaqu", "text_ar": "رَجُلٌ اَخْلَقُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mina AlmaAli", "text_ar": "مِنَ المَالِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A man destitute of property."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) And it is said in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "layosa Alfaqiyra faqiyru AlmaAli A_in~amaA", "text_ar": "لَيْسَ الفَقِيرَ فَقِيرُ المَالِ اـِنَّمَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alfaqiyru AlA^axolaqu Alkasobi", "text_ar": "الفَقِيرُ الاَخْلَقُ الكَسْبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e. (assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The poor in respect of property is not the poor the poor is only"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 803}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he who has no good deeds for which he will be rewarded"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the world to come. (TA, in two places.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^axolaqu", "text_ar": "الاَخْلَقُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The exterior of a horse's hoof."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(JK.) ―         -b4-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xaloqaA='u", "text_ar": "خَلْقَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (JK, S, K,) applied to a woman, (JK, S,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Impervia coëunti;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K, TA;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xul~aqN", "text_ar": "خُلَّقٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Ibn-'Abbád, K.) ―         -b5-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xaliqN", "text_ar": "خَلِقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b6-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlxaloqaA='u", "text_ar": "الخَلْقَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[used as a subst.]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The sky;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because of its smoothness and evenness. (TA.) ―         -b7-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The side"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a camel &c. (K.) One says also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Darabotu xaloqaA='a janobihi", "text_ar": "ضَرَبْتُ خَلْقَا=ءَ جَنْبِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA [in the CK"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ElY xaloqaA'a janobihi", "text_ar": "على خَلْقَاءَ جَنْبِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "])"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I struck the outer part of his side."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b8-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The interior"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, K, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and smooth part"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, TA,) of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gaAr", "text_ar": "غَار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) i. e., of [the upper part of the interior of the mouth, or] what is termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlgaAru AlA^aEolaY", "text_ar": "الغَارُ الاَعْلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Lth, TA;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlxulayoqaA='u", "text_ar": "الخُلَيْقَا=ءُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[the dim. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlxaloqaA='u", "text_ar": "الخَلْقَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Lth, K, TA:) or both signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what appears"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gAr", "text_ar": "غار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and the dim. form is that which is predominant in this case. (TA.) ―         -b9-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The part"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the forehead"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that is even"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(JK, K, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and smooth;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlxulayoqaA='u", "text_ar": "الخُلَيْقَا=ءُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (JK, K, TA.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suHibuwA EalaY xaloqaAwaAti jibaAhihimo", "text_ar": "سُحِبُوا عَلَى خَلْقَاوَاتِ جِبَاهِهِمْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They were dragged along upon the even and smooth parts of their foreheads"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA [in which this is said to be tropical]) ―         -b10-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alfarasi", "text_ar": "الفَرَسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xulayoqaA='u", "text_ar": "خُلَيْقَا=ءُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "That"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "part"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the horse which is like the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eironiyn", "text_ar": "عِرْنِين"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upper part of the nose"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of man;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the part where the forehead of the horse meets the narrow portion of the bone of the nose:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "AO says that the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xulayoqaAwaAni", "text_ar": "خُلَيْقَاوَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the face of the horse are [the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "two parts"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "where his forehead meets the bone of his nose, on the right and left of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xulayoqaA='", "text_ar": "خُلَيْقَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sloping towards the eye;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xulayoqaA='", "text_ar": "خُلَيْقَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is [the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "part"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "between the eyes;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and some call it the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xaloqaA='", "text_ar": "خَلْقَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a A^axolaqa bika A^ano tafoEala ka*aA", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ اَخْلَقَ بِكَ اَنْ تَفْعَلَ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a phrase mentioned by Ks, as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily the most apt, meet, 